On Sun, Feb 21, 2010 at 4:31 AM, Kevin Guarnotta <kguarnotta(-at-)usa.net> wrote:

> So if the horn goes off with the ground wire connected, there is a short
 somewhere in the steering column, is that right? Usually insulation
wearing off the wire.

That's right.

> Searching the archives, it seems like the solution may be to replace the
 wire in the steering column. I can see the top, but the bottom looks
 impossible to get at without removing the steering box.

You will have some flex. After you disconnect the bracket to the
dashboard, the steering column will drop. If not enough, you can
disconnect it from the rubber "universal joint" just below the floor.

